post_text: On Monday, the USD 210 Board of Education was presented a draft plan for the 2020-2021 school year. Over 20 district teachers and administrators spent nearly a week, developing this draft to provide high quality learning opportunities for students, in a flexible, safe, and healthy environment. It is the goal of the Board of Education to provide in-person learning as long as it is safe and in the best interest of staff and students. USD 210 recognizes that families have diverse health needs, and will work to provide opportunities that best suit those unique situations. The Board will meet next week to continue discussing these phases. Additional information will be released once the details of the specific plan are worked out.

post_text:
Today, the Kansas State Board of Education, in a 5-5 vote, revoked the Executive Order mandating school start after Labor Day. This allows local school districts to determine when school will start.

This week, a group of USD 210 staff and administrators have been meeting to formulate the district's plans for the upcoming school year. We recognize that a student learns best in a face to face environment with instruction from a teacher. We are committed to finding a way for this to happen in a safe manner, for all of our students.

We know many parents and students are anxiously awaiting information on when and how school will start and look. We hope to have these details ironed out to be able to communicate with families by the end of this month.

post_text: HHS Graduation is scheduled for Saturday, July 11th at 9:00 am at the football stadium. We are encouraging families to sit in family units and socially distance from other family units (minimum 6 feet apart). Seating will be available in both the home and visitor stands. We are also making available the East side of the football field for any who wish to bring their own lawn chairs. Masks will be available for anyone who wishes to take one. We encourage families and the community to help us celebrate our wonderful seniors safely.

post_text:
2021 USD 210 Teacher of the Year Nominations
Being Accepted

USD 210 is accepting nominations for the 2021 Kansas Teacher of the Year. This program identifies, recognizes, and utilizes representatives of excellent teaching in the elementary and secondary classrooms. Its mission is to build and utilize a network of exemplary teachers who are leaders in the improvement of schools, student performance, and the teaching profession.

To nominate a teacher, simply submit a brief letter that includes their name and why they should be a nominee to: arlet.estrada@usd210.org

The district will accept nominations through April 8th, 2020. A nominating committee will narrow the applications to one teacher who will represent our district in the Kansas Teacher of the Year Program (KTOY).
text:
2021 USD 210 Teacher of the Year Nominations
Being Accepted

USD 210 is accepting nominations for the 2021 Kansas Teacher of the Year. This program identifies, recognizes, and utilizes representatives of excellent teaching in the elementary and secondary classrooms. Its mission is to build and utilize a network of exemplary teachers who are leaders in the improvement of schools, student performance, and the teaching profession.

To nominate a teacher, simply submit a brief letter that includes their name and why they should be a nominee to: arlet.estrada@usd210.org

The district will accept nominations through April 8th, 2020. A nominating committee will narrow the applications to one teacher who will represent our district in the Kansas Teacher of the Year Program (KTOY).
